title: Cash Me Ousside girl slams 'attention seeking' Kylie Jenner and rows with Soulja Boy on Twitter
text:
Showbiz Cash Me Ousside girl slams 'attention seeking' Kylie Jenner and rows with Soulja Boy on Twitter Danielle Bregoli became an internet sensation after her appearance on US chat show Dr. Phil went viral - and it looks like she's doing anything to try and stay relevant Share Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now 'Cash Me Ousside Girl' SLAMS Kylie Jenner in radio interview Share this video Get daily updates directly to your inbox + Subscribe Thank you for subscribing! Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email 
Cash Me Ousside girl Danielle Bregoli has accused Kylie Jenner of trying to seek attention "so bad". 
Yes, the girl who is famous for nothing - apart from appearing on US show Dr. Phil - took aim at the youngest Kardashian-Jenner sister this week. 
Declaring war on the teen, the 13-year-old told radio station Power 106 : “I don’t like her. Like the way that she does s**t, like urgh… It seems like she wants attention so bad. Like little b**ch would do anything.” 
She continued: “How do you go from f**king lips the size of a twig and a body that looks like a f**king paperclip and now you look like a hourglass? Like man, what the f**k?!” Kylie Jenner, Tyga (Photo: Splash News) Kylie Jenner, Alexander Wang show, Fall Winter 2017, New York Fashion Week (Photo: Rex Features) Danielle first appeared on Dr. Phil last year (Photo: REUTERS/Twitter) 
Clearly not worried about what Kylie thinks, Danielle continued: "B**ch come meet me at the Roosevelt. Wassup? I'm right here." 
And not content with just taking aim at Kylie, she then got into a war of words - unclear what about - with Soulja Boy, 26, on Twitter. Kylie Jenner and Tyga go to dinner at Nobu in New York City, New York (Photo: Splash News) Kylie Jenner (Photo: Instagram/KylieJenner) 
"F**k you @souljaboy," she wrote, to which he replied, "F**k you too little ugly b**ch." 
But she apparently had the final word, firing back: "I made more money this week than you did last year." 
Howbow dah?
